01068    {
01069       // Inspect the data members of an object of class TkObject.
01070       typedef ::ROOT::Shadow::TkObject ShadowClass;
01071       ShadowClass *sobj = (ShadowClass*)obj;
01072       if (sobj) { } // Dummy usage just in case there is no datamember.
01073 
01074       TClass *R__cl  = ::ROOT::GenerateInitInstanceLocal((const ::TkObject*)0x0)->GetClass();
01075       Int_t R__ncp = strlen(R__parent);
01076       if (R__ncp || R__cl || R__insp.IsA()) { }
01077       R__insp.Inspect(R__cl, R__parent, "name[50]", sobj->name);
01078       R__insp.Inspect(R__cl, R__parent, "pos", &sobj->pos);
01079       sobj->pos.ShowMembers(R__insp, strcat(R__parent,"pos.")); R__parent[R__ncp] = 0;
01080       R__insp.Inspect(R__cl, R__parent, "rot", (void*)&sobj->rot);
01081       ::ROOT::GenericShowMembers("AMSRotMat", (void*)&sobj->rot, R__insp, strcat(R__parent,"rot."),false);
01082       R__parent[R__ncp] = 0;
01083       R__insp.Inspect(R__cl, R__parent, "posA", &sobj->posA);
01084       sobj->posA.ShowMembers(R__insp, strcat(R__parent,"posA.")); R__parent[R__ncp] = 0;
01085       R__insp.Inspect(R__cl, R__parent, "rotA", (void*)&sobj->rotA);
01086       ::ROOT::GenericShowMembers("AMSRotMat", (void*)&sobj->rotA, R__insp, strcat(R__parent,"rotA."),false);
01087       R__parent[R__ncp] = 0;
01088    }
